	<h3 id="section_whats_new_3_0_0">KVS v3.0.0 [17.12.2012]</h3>
	<h4>Conversion and storage engine</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>
			CDN integration was completely re-implemented. Previously KVS supported limited CDN providers, but starting
			from v3 you can use any CDN provider. In order to do that, CDN provider should implement API script so that
			KVS can use it (redirect to content + invalidation).
		</li>
		<li>
			Added a new function to completely check content serving from a particular storage server. Older versions
			had functions "test direct link", "test protected link" and "test streaming". The new version grouped these
			functions into one option, which can do everything automatically and display summary for you. All checks
			consider different content protection options: direct links to video files should not work, direct links
			to album files should work only for publicly allowed formats and etc. This new option lets you easily check
			the valid configuration of each storage server.
		</li>
		<li>
			Enhanced integration between main server and remote conversion servers. Main server now displays the
			configured server libraries and their echo responses for every conversion server. It is also possible to
			specify conversion server timezone offset if needed in order to prevent fake errors.
		</li>
		<li>
			Video formats were extended with ability to configure per-sponsor duration limits using sponsor custom
			fields (similar to customization of different watermarks for different sponsors).
		</li>
		<li>
			When a multipart trailer is created, it is now possible to configure so that the last trailer part is
			taken from the end of last fragment. Previously all trailer parts were taken from the beginning of
			fragments, including the last part.
		</li>
		<li>
			Dramatically optimized the way of creating many similar trailers with different size / quality options.
		</li>
		<li>
			When a video format is being re-created via mass edit, it is now possible to disable watermark for this
			operation. This option makes great sense if another format file acts as a source file and it already has
			watermark - in this case no double watermarking will take place.
		</li>
		<li>
			Added ability to delete timeline screenshots for any video format, where timeline screenshots are disabled.
			You can use this option if you want to get more free space and you don't need timeline screenshots for this
			format anymore.
		</li>
		<li>
			Thumb creation logic was completely rewritten to reduce the number of subsequent ImageMagick operations
			and optimize the resulting image quality.
		</li>
		<li>
			Background tasks logging was improved. Ability to see done % was added for all tasks with considering
			conversion server execution part.
		</li>
		<li>
			Formats for video screenshots were extended with additional ImageMagick options field, which is intended
			to be used for all screenshots that are uploaded manually. Previously for all manually uploaded screenshots
			there were no any ImageMagick options applied (only resize and watermark were applied) so that there was
			no any ability to post-process the uploaded screenshots with ImageMagick. Now this is fixed.
		</li>
		<li>
			Added ability to create video screenshots format with source size (not resized to any particular size). In
			order to do that you should specify predefined word <b>source</b> as a format size.
		</li>
		<li>
			Each background task now has its own log.
		</li>
	</ul>
	<h4>Premium access</h4>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Added support for token-based access in addition to time-limited access. Tokens are available for standard
			(non-premium) members and can be purchased via payment system or "awarded" via community actions. Members
			can spent their available tokens to get premium access to particular content. At the same type members will
			remain in standard / active status, but when accessing the purchased content their status will be
			considered as premium. According to that, you can combine time-limited and token-based access options on
			your site without any restrictions.
		</li>
		<li>
			To facilitate the extended memberzone functionality KVS now has a separate Memberzone Settings page, where
			you can enable token based access for particular types of content (separate settings for standard / premium
			videos and albums) and configure their default prices. For any particular video / album you can manually
			override its price using standalone editing or mass edit.
		</li>
		<li>
			Memberzone Settings page also contains ability to configure awards for members' activity. An award is the
			number of granted tokens for a particular action, such as initial signup, avatar upload, posting a comment
			(with ability to limit minimum length), uploading a video (with ability to limit minimum duration),
			creating an album (with ability to limit minimum image count).
